      <title>RE: HowTo use LDAP/ActiveDirectory for Authentication and Authorization</title>
      <link>http://community.zenoss.org/docs/DOC-2510#comments-6839</link>
      <description>&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyStart:59075e2a-4c1f-40de-96a2-0ce96677ba50] --&gt;&lt;div class="jive-rendered-content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Created a script.&amp;#160; Do not know if anyone is interested.&amp;#160; Here it is.&amp;#160; Tested on 4.2.4 auto-deploy and RHEL 6.4 x64.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#!/bin/bash&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#Install LDAP support for Zenoss&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#Jeff Creek - 9/10/2013&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ $USER = "zenoss" ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "logged in as zenoss"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;else&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Must be ran while logged in as zenoss"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;exit&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;installed=`rpm -qa | grep python-ldap`&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo $installed&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ $installed ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "phython-ldap is installed....\n..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;else&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo -e "Manually run 'yum -y install python-ldap' as root.&amp;#160; Then run this script."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;exit&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Making directories..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;mkdir $ZENHOME/python&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;mkdir $ZENHOME/python/lib&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;mkdir $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;mkdir $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6/site-packages&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Creating links..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ln -s /usr/lib64/python2.6/site-packages/ldap/ $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6/site-packages/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ln -s /usr/lib64/python2.6/site-packages/ldapurl.py $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6/site-packages/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ln -s /usr/lib64/python2.6/site-packages/ldapurl.pyc $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6/site-packages/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ln -s /usr/lib64/python2.6/site-packages/_ldap.so $ZENHOME/python/lib/python2.6/site-packages/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;cd /home/zenoss&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Downloading..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="http://www.dataflake.org/software/ldapuserfolder/ldapuserfolder_2.12/LDAPUserFolder-2.12.tgz/download"&gt;http://www.dataflake.org/software/ldapuserfolder/ldapuserfolder_2.12/LDAPUserFolder-2.12.tgz/download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt; -O LDAPUserFolder-2.12.tgz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="http://www.dataflake.org/software/ldapmultiplugins/ldapmultiplugins_1.7/LDAPMultiPlugins-1.7.tgz/download"&gt;http://www.dataflake.org/software/ldapmultiplugins/ldapmultiplugins_1.7/LDAPMultiPlugins-1.7.tgz/download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt; -O LDAPMultiPlugins-1.7.tgz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Extracting..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;tar -zxvf LDAPUserFolder*.tgz -C $ZENHOME/Products&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;tar -zxvf LDAPMultiPlugins*.tgz -C $ZENHOME/Products&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -e "Now login to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="http://servername:8080"&gt;http://servername:8080&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Restart zopectl&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Login to http:/servername:8080/zport/manage as an administrator&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click acl_users on the left side.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the list next to Add, select LDAP Multi Plugin.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configure the LDAP settings for you environment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click Add.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enable LDAP cache.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\ta.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click on acl_users&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tb.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;In the upper right corner next to Add select RAM Cache Manager&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tc.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Give the Cache Manager a name &amp;ndash; LDAP Cache&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\td.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click Add&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\te.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click on LDAP Cache in the list&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tf.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click on the Associate tab&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tg.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click on LDAP Multi Plugin in the list&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\th.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click Locate&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\ti.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click the check box next to the LDAP Authentication object you created earlier&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tj.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Click Save Changes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click on acl_users then LDAP Authentication.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click the check box next to Authentication, User_Enumeration and Roles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click Update.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click the Contents tab.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click acl_users.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make sure that Group Mapping is set to "Manually map LDAP groups to Zope roles".&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click the Groups tab.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Scroll to the "LDAP group to Zope role mappings" section.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Next to My LDAP Group select your admin group.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Next to &amp;#8230;to Zope Rule select Manager.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click Add."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyEnd:59075e2a-4c1f-40de-96a2-0ce96677ba50] --&gt;</description>
