      <title>RE: HowTo use LDAP/ActiveDirectory for Authentication and Authorization</title>
      <link>http://community.zenoss.org/docs/DOC-2510#comments-7430</link>
      <description>&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyStart:61676b98-6ead-4136-9c2e-7e8419aade40] --&gt;&lt;div class="jive-rendered-content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just wanted to post a similar script to Jeffs but doesn't need symlinks for python 2.6.&amp;#160; This includes steps for setting up LDAPS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote class="jive-quote"&gt;&lt;p&gt;#!/bin/bash&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;# Install LDAP Support for Zenoss&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;# Taken from this post &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="http://blogs.oregonstate.edu/sig/2013/03/28/enabling-ldap-authentication-in-zenoss-core-4-2-and-centos-6/"&gt;http://blogs.oregonstate.edu/sig/2013/03/28/enabling-ldap-authentication-in-zenoss-core-4-2-and-centos-6/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;# &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="https://bugs.launchpad.net/ldapuserfolder/+bug/1221624"&gt;https://bugs.launchpad.net/ldapuserfolder/+bug/1221624&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Please make sure OpenLDAP is configured with the CA of the Active Directory/LDAP server you are connecting to for secure communication"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;# Place the CA cert into /etc/openldap/certs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;# OpenLDAP needs to be configued to use the CA with the following configuration /etc/openldap/ldap.conf&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;## Start Config File ##&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;## LDAP Defaults&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt; &lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;## See ldap.conf(5) for details&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;## This file should be world readable but not world writable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##BASE&amp;#160;&amp;#160; dc=example,dc=com&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##URI&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; ldap://ldap.example.com ldap://ldap-master.example.com:666&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##SIZELIMIT&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 12&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##TIMELIMIT&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; 15&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;##DEREF&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; never&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#TLS_REQCERT never&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#TLS_CACERTDIR /etc/openldap/certs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;#TLS_CACERT /etc/openldap/certs/&amp;lt;YOUR CA ROOT CERT&amp;gt;.crt&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;## End Config File ##&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Installing required packages..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo yum -y install gcc python-devel openssl-devel openldap-devel&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to install required packages.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Downloading required auth plugins..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'mkdir -p /home/zenoss/ldap-auth'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to create ldap-auth directory.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'wget -P /home/zenoss/ldap-auth &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/P/Products.LDAPMultiPlugins/Products.LDAPMultiPlugins-1.14.tar.gz"&gt;https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/P/Products.LDAPMultiPlugins/Products.LDAPMultiPlugins-1.14.tar.gz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to download LDAPMultiPlugins.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'wget -P /home/zenoss/ldap-auth &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/P/Products.LDAPUserFolder/Products.LDAPUserFolder-2.24.tar.gz"&gt;https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/P/Products.LDAPUserFolder/Products.LDAPUserFolder-2.24.tar.gz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to download LDAPUserFolder.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'wget -P /home/zenoss/ldap-auth &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/p/python-ldap/python-ldap-2.4.10.tar.gz"&gt;https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/p/python-ldap/python-ldap-2.4.10.tar.gz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to download python-ldap.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Running python easy_install as zenoss user..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'easy_install /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/Products.LDAPMultiPlugins-1.14.tar.gz'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to easy_install /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/LDAPMultiPlugins.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'easy_install /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/Products.LDAPUserFolder-2.24.tar.gz'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to easy_install LDAPUserFolder.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Creating patch file for security declaration of non-existing method"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;cat &amp;lt;&amp;lt; EOF &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/LDAPUserFolder.patch&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;--- a/Products/LDAPUserFolder/LDAPUserFolder.py&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;+++ b/Products/LDAPUserFolder/LDAPUserFolder.py&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;@@ -1990,7 +1990,7 @@ class LDAPUserFolder(BasicUserFolder):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; return getattr(conn, '_uri', '-- not connected --')&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; security.declareProtected(manage_users, 'getEncryptedPassword')&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;+&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; security.declareProtected(manage_users, 'getEncryptedBindPassword')&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; def getEncryptedBindPassword(self):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; """ Return a hashed bind password for safe use in forms etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; """&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;EOF&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Applying LDAPUserFolder patch.."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;# Run this as the zenoss user to have the correct path for $ZENHOME -- need a way to not hardcode this&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo patch /vol0/opt/zenoss/lib/python2.7/site-packages/Products.LDAPUserFolder-2.24-py2.7.egg/Products/LDAPUserFolder/LDAPUserFolder.py &amp;lt; /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/LDAPUserFolder.patch&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to patch LDAPUserFolder.py.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo runuser -l zenoss -c 'easy_install /home/zenoss/ldap-auth/python-ldap-2.4.10.tar.gz'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;rc=$?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;if [ ${rc} != 0 ]; then&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; echo "Unable to easy_install python-ldap.&amp;#160; Error Code: ${?}"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; exit 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Restarting zenoss..."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;sudo /etc/init.d/zenoss restart&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo "Log into &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-external-small" href="https://`hostname`/zport/manage"&gt;https://`hostname`/zport/manage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt; to configure ldap authentication"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo "Click acl_users in the tree on the left side.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the list next to Add on the right, select ActiveDirectory Multi Plugin from the dropdown and Click Add.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configure the ActiveDirectory settings for you environment and click Add.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\ta:&amp;#160; ID: Active Directory Authentication&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tb:&amp;#160; Title: Active Directory Authentication&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tc:&amp;#160; LDAP Server[:port]: &amp;lt;Domain Controller&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\td:&amp;#160; Use SSL: &amp;lt;checked&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\te:&amp;#160; Read-only: &amp;lt;checked&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tf:&amp;#160; Login Name Attribute: Windows Login Name (sAMAccountName)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tg:&amp;#160; Users Base DN: &lt;span style="font-family: 'Lucida Grande', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;OU=Foo,dc=example,dc=net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\th:&amp;#160; Scope: SUBTREE&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\ti:&amp;#160; Group storage: Groups stored on LDAP server&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tj:&amp;#160; Groups Base DN: &lt;span style="font-family: 'Lucida Grande', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;OU=Bar,dc=example,dc=net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tk: Scope: SUBTREE&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;\tl:&amp;#160; Manager DN: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="jive-link-email-small" href="mailto:user@example.net"&gt;user@example.net&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tm:&amp;#160; Password: &amp;lt;password&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\tn:&amp;#160; User password encryption: SHA&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\to:&amp;#160; Default User Roles: Anonymous&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="min-hei